nd a structured decision tree to guide the adoption journey. \nA..Decision Tree  \nThe decision tree guides organizations through critical checkpoints for Agentic AI \nimplementation. Starting with data readiness assessment, it branches through \ninfrastructure evaluation, talent assessment, and ethical considerations, ultimately \nleading to industry-specific implementation paths. \nIndustry specific \nreadiness \nData \nReadiness\nInfrastructure \nevaluation\nTalent \nAssessment \nComputational \nresources \nEthical \nFramework \n42\nAGENTIC AI FOR EXECUTIVES\nDecision Tree  \nOrganization AI Implementation\nIterative\nlevel\nData\nReadiness\nData collection \nStrategy\nInsufficient data\nInfrastructure\nevaluation\nSufficient data\nComputational \nresources\nEthical\nFramework\nSkill\nProficiency\nIndustry\nspecific\nreadiness\nData\nQuality\nmeets \nthreshold?\nData Quality \nImprovement\nAdequateInadequate Yes\nTeam formation\nUnestablished\n\nComputational \nresources\nEthical\nFramework\nSkill\nProficiency\nIndustry\nspecific\nreadiness\nData\nQuality\nmeets \nthreshold?\nData Quality \nImprovement\nAdequateInadequate Yes\nTeam formation\nUnestablished\nEstablished\nTalent \nacquisition\nstrategy\nImplement Cont monitoring\nM H F R C\nInsuffient\nSkill Gap Suffiecient \nTalent\nNo\nTraining\nUpskilling\nIntra Upgrade\nCloud Setup\nTalent\nAssessment\nCompliance Gov\nFramework\nDevelop AI Ethics\nData Standardization\nM - Manufacturing  H - Healthcare  F - Financial Services  R - Retail  C - Construction\nAdequate\nResource\nAugmentation\nPlan\nInadequate\n43\nAGENTIC AI FOR EXECUTIVES\nB. Industry-Wise Readiness  \nBefore an organization moves forward with implementing Agentic AI, it is crucial to \nassess its readiness across several key areas. These evaluation parameters serve as \na checklist, helping organizations ensure they have the right foundational elements in \nplace before proceeding with agentic AI adoption. By evaluating each of these\n\nAgentic 